      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITE IT UP LOUIE (7) settled well back when 8 lengths from the winner in sixth over 1207m at this track last start, a less impressive effort than her fifth at this track the run before. Beautifully placed and is sure to be there at the finish. WHAT'S TO DO (5) is close to breaking through after three consecutive placings, the latest coming when second over 1609m at this track (Dirt) after being in the firing line all the way. Taking on a better line-up this time but she has the ability to mix it with them. PAYTON'S BEAUTY (1) is a distance specialist who missed the placings two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1207m at this track, beaten 6 lengths. Needs to be at her best to beat this field but she is up to the challenge. COURTNEY FAY (2) has not won for a long while. Last raced on March 22 when beaten 9 lengths into seventh at this track (Dirt) over 1609m after she gave away a big start. Well placed and can play a prominent role.",
